cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

The paper proposes a method for counting and localizing objects in videos recorded by drones, which involves computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces spatially regularized constraints into the network, which is related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) the second likely category. The proposed method involves deep learning and neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the evaluation of the proposed method on a new dataset, which involves data management and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category. Finally, the proposed method is applied to videos, which involves multimedia and video processing, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category.
